title: Manchester falls at home;Trine triumphs on the road
text:
Manchester falls at home;Trine triumphs on the road 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive October 24, 2015 Updated Oct 24, 2015 at 11:39 PM EDT 
UNDATED (21 Alive) - Manchester dropped a football decision to Bluffton on Saturday at home, while Trine won a scoring free for all on the road at Albion. 
Logan Haston ran for a touchdown and JerronJackson caught a pass for another, but Manchester still lost 28-20 to visiting Bluffton.

Gage Corner's second touchdown catch of the game with 21 seconds remaining following a successful onside kick lifted Trine to a 55-51 win at Albion. 
Trine got huge games from Corner, who caught 13 passes for 186 yards, from quarterback Brandon Rooze, who threw for 272 yards and three touchdowns, and from Mark Wilson, who rushed 46 times for 327 yards and scored five touchdowns.
